a. Creating a taskforce committee composed of particular personnel in the accounting and treasurer’s office in coordination with the Punong Barangays who will strictly follow up and monitor the compliance of the barangays in terms of the following:

•	preparation and maintenance of a hard bound/ or compiled cash books of the composite barangays; 

•	ensure that all the cashbooks of the AOs are updated and duly certified to determine the correct accountability in any given period;
•	timely submission of transaction documents (RCDs, RCRs, DVs, LRs, etc) of the Barangays to the Accounting Office;

•	conduct of quarterly reconciliation between the MTO and MAO for the LGU and between the BT and MAO for the composite barangays; and

•	timely and proper bonding of AOs in the Municipality and Barangays.

b. The Municipal Accountant and the assigned personnel from the accounting office composing the taskforce to proactively and consistently send demand letters to all barangays found to be delayed in the report’s submission, copy furnished this office and ensure that subsidiary ledgers are prepared for the MTO AOs and BT AOs to allow quarterly reconciliation of records;

c. The Accounting Office, with strict and proper monitoring of the compliance of barangays, impose penalties to AOs committing the same non-compliance with the rules and regulations and provide rewards/incentives to all those complying AOs; and
d. The Office of the Mayor encourage reporting of accomplishments or feedback mechanisms from the taskforce created to the LCE or assigned official to keep track of the progress made and challenges encountered in implementing the same.

