We recommended that the Management assign personnel for the constant monitoring and general supervision over each component Barangays to ensure that every barangay act within the scope of their prescribed powers and functions by:

a. Monitoring their submission of reports to the Municipality complete with the required supporting documentation within the deadline set by the Municipal Accountant and as prescribed by the Manual on Financial Management of Barangays and send demand letters, if warranted;

b. Conducting re-orientation seminar focusing on the Appendix C of the manual which provides for the Matrix of Reports and Forms showing the record/report title, who shall submit or accomplish the report, number of copies to be distributed and to whom it will be distributed, the frequency and due date of submission and the remarks or purpose of the record/report, to know the extent of their duties and responsibilities; 

d. Require explanation/ justification from Barangays who still failed to comply despite constant monitoring and supervision.

