observations.recommendation:
We recommended and management agreed that the Local School Board:
a) Strictly comply with the provisions of Section 272 of the LGC in identifying programs/projects/ activities chargeable tot SEF; 
b) Be more circumspect and judicious in charging DepEd-related activities and co- curricular activities against SEF, considering that DepEd has its own budget.

We recommended and management agreed to the following:
a. Limit the utilization of the Special Education Fund to the allowed expenses as prescribed by rules and regulations;
b. Be more circumspect and judicious in charging DECS-related activities and co-curricular activities against SEF, considering that DepEd has its own budget for its Maintenance and Operating Expenses.

We recommended to management the following remedial measures:
a. The Municipal Rural Health Unit (MRHU) provide the Municipal Accounting Office copies of the Invoice Receipts for Property so that the drugs and medicines, medical, dental and laboratory supplies, vaccines, other supplies and PPE received from DOH will be recognized in the books of the Municipality;
b. The MRHU to prepare a report on the utilization of the commodities received from DOH-CAR duly supported with distribution lists and acknowledgment receipts, to be forwarded to the Municipal Accountant as his basis in recognizing inventory items issued in the books of accounts, copy furnished the Audit Teams of the Municipality of Tuba and DOH-CAR.
